---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { t } from '../../i18n/translations.js';

const locale = 'en';
---

<Layout title="About the Forum - GOSIM AI Vision Forum">

	<main>
		<section class="page-header">
			<div class="container">
				<h1>{t('about.title', locale)}</h1>
				<p>{t('about.subtitle', locale)}</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="content-section">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="content-grid">
					<div class="main-content">
						<h2>Forum Background</h2>
						<p>
							GOSIM Global Open-Source Innovation Meetup has always adhered to the core spirit of open source — 
							with openness and inclusiveness as the foundation, global collaboration as the link, and community-driven as the driving force. 
							Based on this philosophy, we unite multiple forces to jointly launch the AI Vision Forum, 
							focusing on the critical question: "What core value can AI create for humanity?"
						</p>

						<p>
							In recent years, large language models (LLMs), generative AI, and intelligent agents have rapidly evolved. 
							In high-intelligence task domains once exclusive to humans—from mathematical proofs and code writing to literary creation and artistic expression—
							top AI models continuously break performance boundaries, refreshing our understanding of machine intelligence.
						</p>

						<blockquote>
							This breakthrough creates complex ripples in human society: on one hand, it seems humanity has found the key to unlocking cosmic mysteries 
							and opening the door to the next generation of civilization; on the other hand, as AI continues advancing in "human-exclusive" intellectual territories, 
							people deeply worry: will human unique creativity and emotional perception be replaced?
						</blockquote>

						<h2>Forum Objectives</h2>
						<p>
							Around these questions, this AI Vision Forum jointly initiated by GOSIM and AJTIS 
							brings together representatives from top universities, research institutions and enterprises worldwide, 
							adopting an invitation-only, closed-door, small-scale deep interaction mechanism.
						</p>

						<p>
							The forum particularly focuses on the positive value of artificial intelligence in the human experience dimension, 
							focusing on key areas such as educational innovation, cultural creation, emotional companionship, and technological equity, 
							deeply exploring how AI products balance functionality and ethics, efficiency and warmth in practical applications.
						</p>

						<h2>Core Philosophy</h2>
						<p>
							We advocate a paradigm shift: making AI not just a technical empowerment tool, but result-oriented, 
							effectively responding to and solving core human concerns. We believe that truly meaningful AI should be able to understand human emotional needs, 
							respect cultural diversity, promote social equity, and play a positive role in education, healthcare, artistic creation and other fields.
						</p>

						<p>
							In activity design, the forum features "Technical Products" and "Artistic Creativity" dual-unit AIGC Spotlight 
							global showcase, aiming to build a thought community spanning technical logic and humanistic perspectives.
						</p>

						<h2>International Cooperation</h2>
						<p>
							This event is not only a cross-boundary deep dialogue, but also an important practice for China and Europe to reshape consensus on AI social responsibility and value orientation, 
							committed to creating an international cooperation platform with continuity, influence and ethical deliberation tension.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="sidebar">
						<div class="info-card">
							<h3>Event Details</h3>
							<ul class="event-info">
								<li><strong>Date:</strong> September 12, 2025 (Friday)</li>
								<li><strong>Location:</strong> Hangzhou, China</li>
								<li><strong>Scale:</strong> 70-100 participants</li>
								<li><strong>Format:</strong> Invitation-only closed exchange</li>
								<li><strong>Language:</strong> Chinese & English</li>
							</ul>
						</div>

						<div class="info-card">
							<h3>Organizers</h3>
							<ul class="organizers">
								<li>GOSIM Global Open-Source Innovation Meetup</li>
								<li>AJTIS</li>
							</ul>
						</div>

						<div class="info-card">
							<h3>Forum Format</h3>
							<ul class="format-list">
								<li>Keynote Speeches</li>
								<li>Deep Roundtable Discussions</li>
								<li>AIGC Spotlight Showcase</li>
								<li>Cross-disciplinary Dialogue</li>
								<li>Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner Networking</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="outcomes-section">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>Expected Outcomes</h2>
				<div class="outcomes-grid">
					<div class="outcome-card">
						<h3>China-Europe AI for Good Initiative</h3>
						<p>Release the "China-Europe Artificial Intelligence Technology for Good Initiative Draft", building a consensus document centered on "humanistic values guiding AI development"</p>
					</div>
					<div class="outcome-card">
						<h3>AIGC Spotlight Mechanism</h3>
						<p>Establish permanent mechanism to promote project implementation and cross-border cooperation, building international recommendation and support mechanisms</p>
					</div>
					<div class="outcome-card">
						<h3>Trinity Integration Paradigm</h3>
						<p>Form a "technology + humanities + governance" trinity integration forum paradigm, exploring sustainable dialogue mechanisms for future cooperation</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	/* Page Header */
	.page-header {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
		color: white;
		padding: 80px 0 60px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.page-header h1 {
		font-size: 3rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.page-header p {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		opacity: 0.9;
	}

	/* Content Section */
	.content-section {
		padding: 80px 0;
		background: #f8f9fa;
	}

	.content-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
		gap: 40px;
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.main-content h2 {
		color: #2d3748;
		font-size: 2rem;
		margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.main-content h2:first-child {
		margin-top: 0;
	}

	.main-content p {
		color: #4a5568;
		line-height: 1.8;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		font-size: 1.1rem;
	}

	.main-content blockquote {
		border-left: 4px solid #667eea;
		padding-left: 1.5rem;
		margin: 2rem 0;
		color: #2d3748;
		font-style: italic;
		background: rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.05);
		padding: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
	}

	/* Sidebar */
	.sidebar {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 24px;
	}

	.info-card {
		background: white;
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
	}

	.info-card h3 {
		color: #2d3748;
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.event-info,
	.organizers,
	.format-list {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.event-info li,
	.organizers li,
	.format-list li {
		padding: 0.5rem 0;
		color: #4a5568;
		border-bottom: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
	}

	.event-info li:last-child,
	.organizers li:last-child,
	.format-list li:last-child {
		border-bottom: none;
	}

	.event-info strong {
		color: #2d3748;
	}

	/* Outcomes Section */
	.outcomes-section {
		padding: 80px 0;
		background: white;
	}

	.outcomes-section h2 {
		text-align: center;
		color: #2d3748;
		font-size: 2.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.outcomes-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
		gap: 30px;
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.outcome-card {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f6f9fc 0%, #ffffff 100%);
		border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 30px;
		transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
	}

	.outcome-card:hover {
		transform: translateY(-5px);
		box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
	}

	.outcome-card h3 {
		color: #667eea;
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.outcome-card p {
		color: #4a5568;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	/* Responsive Design */
	@media (max-width: 968px) {
		.content-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.page-header h1 {
			font-size: 2rem;
		}

		.outcomes-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}

	/* Container */
	.container {
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 20px;
	}
</style>